<p>I'm using Tooltipster plugin: <a href="http://iamceege.github.io/tooltipster/#demos" rel="nofollow">http://iamceege.github.io/tooltipster/#demos</a> And I'm also using this Drag and Drop plugin: <a href="http://www.jqueryscript.net/other/Easy-Drag-and-Drop-Plugin-For-jQuery-dad-js.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.jqueryscript.net/other/Easy-Drag-and-Drop-Plugin-For-jQuery-dad-js.html</a></p>  <p>I want to trigger a tooltipste when the mouse is over a div which is inside a "movable" div:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;div class="col-lg-3 col-md-3 col-sm-6 col-xs-6 infoBulleItem itemParent"&gt; &lt;div class="testTool"&gt;test test test&lt;/div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;  $('.testTool').tooltipster({ content: $('&lt;span&gt;test&lt;/span&gt;') }); </code></pre>  <p>It works for every .testTool outside my dragable area, but it doesnt for every .testTool inside my dragable area</p>